(63,	'123jdkf',	'John Dory',	'<p></p>\r\n<p>Along with its unusual name, John Dory are also an unusual looking fish. They are easily recognised by their flat bodies, their olive green colour and spines that rise from the dorsal fin. They have the mark of St Peter on the sides of their bodies and are easily recognised by that.&nbsp;In season all year round.</p>\r\n<p>Where does it live: Found all around the world including Africa, Australasia and European waters.</p>\r\n<p>What does it eat: John Dory hunt by sucking prey into their mouths which they make into a tube like structure. They will eat other fish and some Squid.</p>\r\n<p>Size: 32-50cm.</p>',	'john-dory',	1,	1,	1,	NULL,	12.0000,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	10.0000,	1,	'Red',	6,	'S',	'2020-04-12 22:15:00',	'en',	'default',	63,	'2020-04-12 22:15:00',	NULL,	1,	12.0000,	12.0000,	'<p>Freshly caught John Dory</p>',	'',	'',	'',	0.0000,	0.0000,	0.0000),
(64,	'tst123',	'Dover Sole',	'<p></p>\r\n<p>Description: A flat fish, the Dover Sole is a classic British species enjoyed for hundreds of years. They are mousy brown in colour with darker splotches. Scaly along the lateral line with a dark black mark on the pectoral fins. They have a unique pattern on their skin similar to the look of carbon fibre.</p>\r\n<p>Where does it live: Dover Sole live in deep waters but migrate near the shore to spawn.</p>\r\n<p>When is it in season: Dover Sole breed and spawn in the spring so the fish is in its best condition January to March &amp; the from July to January.</p>\r\n<p>What does it eat: Any small creatures found on the seabed. They will eat prawns, worms small shellfish and some crab.</p>\r\n<p>Size: Roughly 30-40cm.</p>',	'dover-sole',	1,	1,	1,	NULL,	11.0000,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	10.0000,	1,	'Red',	6,	'S',	'2020-04-13 03:17:20',	'en',	'default',	64,	'2020-04-13 03:17:20',	NULL,	1,	11.0000,	11.0000,	'<p>Fresh Dover Sole</p>',	'',	'',	'',	0.0000,	0.0000,	0.0000),
